content.description: Easy jug haul to the top of the boulder.  Most dangerous part is topping-out.
content.location: All the way downhill next to the creek.

content.description: Start in an undercling (the same one as "Left Handed S.O.B", but farther to the right), then move straight up on small crimps and smeary feet to a crimp rail right before the lip. Traverse out left to some really good hidden holds over the top lip of the boulder. Be sure to clean off the top really well as it gets dirty very easily.
content.location: On the same boulder as "Left Handed Whore", but more towards the right-hand side of the same face.

content.description: An eliminate on the "flight" boulder. The same undercling start, but go straight from the left hand pinch on up to the top jug, eliminating the middle right hand
content.protection: A pad or two and a spotter
content.location: Directly left of "fight or flight"

content.description: Start and move in pockets to topout.
content.location: Across the stream from Left Handed Whore.

content.description: Sit start with left hand on crimp and right in CD slot, move up using the little arête and the big smile
content.location: Directly across the stream from the drop in, in between The Hangar and the creek

content.description: Sit-down start on the obvious sharp pocket on the bottom left of the Sauna boulder, with very low feet. Line goes up to the small rail then merges with "Right Sauna" on the right after some creative footwork.DON'T GRAB THE ROCKS ON TOP OF THE BOULDER.
content.location: About fifty feet downstream from Fight or Flight. One of the first boulders over the fence from the parking lot. If you can't find it, just walk along the fence. Faces away from the road.

content.description: Start on obvious big rail and move up to topout.
content.location: Right on the other side of the fence by the 2 trash cans.Right side of Sauna boulder.

content.description: Start big left hand side-pull, right hand sloper.    Big reach to small crimp (avoid using the drill slot),    move right hand to other sloping crimp,    reach to lip and do the tenuous top-out.    v2-3 depending on height and style.    Good variations exist: from start head slightly right and up,    using an undercling at mid-wall height (slightly easier, v1/2).
content.location: 10 yards down stream from the Spider Pocket   75 yards down stream from Pinch Arete   in the middle of the stream

content.description: This route is directly above Key Hole Boulder. Start from the ground and use leg bracing to make your way up. You can top out on this route and walk back down to the start area. Moss can be slippery, be careful.
content.location: Use the hemlock loop trail until you get to the restricted area sign. Walk down the path towards the river. On your right side with be Fight Or Flight as you walk down the hill. At the bottom will be Pinch Arete. Walk left of Pinch Arete and you will see Prickly Pickle/Ninja Split Kick on your left right above Key Hole Boulder.

content.description: Avoid catching your ankle in the crack and missing / not committing to the move to the sloper.
content.location: Down the hill from Fight or Flight.

content.description: Top out is a matched hands on top peak and mantle up
content.location: Just left of “fight or flight” 100ft  same set of rocks on that ridge line

content.description:
Fairly juggy but extremely fun and good warm up.  

  Perfect place to bring new outdoor boulders to learn how to spot, climb, and top out safely.  

  Several slightly harder routes and 2 fairly harder routes.  

  Down climb can be a bit tricky but throw a pad down and you should be golden.
content.location: From Parking lot to the left of the swing set:- Walk towards river you should see what looks like a path where water drains. Follow that to the hiking path.- Hop the man-made barricade and continue towards the water. (Edit: The park is adding a gravel path, if you start at the gravel path, you can slowly work your way to the right, once you get to the creek you can walk about 50 ft to the tallest boulder around.)- Zig Zag down (essentially straight but "path" takes you in a zig zag) towards the water, Mother Goose will be the solitary tallest bolder down by the water with a sand landing on the right (downstream).- You've arrived! Rejoice, get your shoes one, and start climbing.From Pinch Arete:- Head downstream over the boulder field and hill.- Stick close to the water and you run right into her.GPS: 41.320125, -81.618864

content.description:
This route runs up the South East arete of the Mother Goose boulder. Start matched on a distinct rail sitting low on the arete. Use various smears and some good technique to work up the arete for a respectable arete boulder. The route goes hands only on the arete, without using the pockets on the far right, but again, there are no rules, so do whatever you want. If you climb this as described, you will only be on the smooth sections of this rock.

 Definitely a more interesting variation than the slab to the right, and something spicier than the dihedral. Named after the inscribed "Bud" at the bottom of the arete and the technique up the arete.
content.location: At Mother Goose boulder, South East Arete, left of the pocketed slab wall that is left of Mother Goose.
